{{nihongo|'''Noriko Senge'''|千家 典子|Senge Noriko|extra= born 22 July 1988}}, formerly {{nihongo|'''Princess Noriko of Takamado'''|典子女王|Noriko Joō}}, is a former member of the {{ill|Imperial House of Japan|en|Imperial House of Japan|WD=Q909452|lt=Imperial House of Japan|1=Imperial House of Japan}} and the second daughter of [[Norihito, Prince Takamado]] and {{ill|Hisako, Princess Takamado|en|Hisako, Princess Takamado|WD=Q448104|lt=Hisako, Princess Takamado|1=Hisako, Princess Takamado}}.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/asia-pacific/2526599.stm|title=Funeral held for Japan's prince|date=29 November 2002|work=[[BBC Online]]|accessdate=28 April 2011}}</ref> She married Kunimaro Senge, a commoner, on 5 October 2014. As a result, she gave up her imperial title and left the {{ill|Imperial House of Japan|en|Imperial House of Japan|WD=Q909452|lt=Japanese Imperial Family|1=Imperial House of Japan}}, as required by law.

